FORMER SA Football Association (Safa) vice president, Mwelo Chief Nonkonyana, has been discouraged from standing in the Safa presidential election in a bid to unseat Danny Jordaan, since he is “ineligible”.Nonkonyana has been on the  campaign trail lately as he plans to oust Jordaan, and claims to have the backing of the right people to topple the former mayor at the association’s elective congress on 24 March. However, the resuscitated Football Transformation Forum (FTF), big backers of Jordaan, told the media yesterday that Nonkonyana “is wasting his time”.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuWR1K3h90ARBegr01RtQGnjsUnOPUDQk_Jz_GZMm67BH7rOFnIT-ogVisxcQWw1mvBGn44bj7_QwiOJZSOLAEAN8s1C3xEeW2AoOZ1sAkOW_0YnTODw1Xj8wS__FsBIHb7mALrpmB3JdnMwINgL8DNxcQMTo2kqvClSMFgXcoKX_OZXSAj3LypKuLEosp-IsucZptHXQXya6g2GIUoyadXGw9EwMc-oKoSQNr1nG7BMVfFHmjWY9hlcos6zFn33o4WHTVuh25yrDPCEU0w\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzOWWtfgDluFREAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
